#align(center, text(17pt)[*Exercise 1.1.3*])

Let $S(a) = 1 + 3 + dots + (2 a - 1), a in NN$.

$S(1) = 2 dot 1 - 1 = 1^2$a

Assume for $n in NN$, $S(n) = 1 + 3 + dots + (2 n - 1) = n^2$, then

$ S(n+1) &= S(n) + (2 (n + 1) - 1) \
    & = n^2 + 2n + 1 \
    & = (n+1)^2 $

